title: Does AMSTAT Have Aircraft Sold Pricing
chunk_text: Premier Plus subscribers can now record sold price information with each transaction. These sold prices are private to your subscription and are not shared with other Amstat users. To enter sold price information, go to the transaction history at the bottom of the aircraft specification page. Each transaction will have an icon to let you add or edit a private sold price. Click the icon, enter your sold price, and click save.

metadata.topic: Entering and Managing Private Sold Price Information

title: Does AMSTAT Have Aircraft Sold Pricing
chunk_text: You also have the option to share sold price information with Amstat. Shared sold price information is only used in an aggregated manner to refine the aircraft valuation tool algorithm. As a Premier Plus subscriber, you already have access to this powerful tool.

metadata.topic: Sharing Sold Price Data to Improve Valuation Algorithms

title: Does AMSTAT Have Aircraft Sold Pricing
chunk_text: The sold price information you've entered is also available in your search results. For transaction searches, click on manage columns and select the fields from the transaction details. For aircraft criteria searches, you'll find this under the last transaction details.

metadata.topic: Accessing and Displaying Sold Price Data in Search Results
